        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 16 at 4:02PM EDT until August 16 at 5:00PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>SVRDTX

The National Weather Service in Detroit/Pontiac has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Livingston County in southeastern Michigan...

* Until 500 PM EDT.

* At 402 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Howell,
moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* This severe thunderstorm will be near...
Brighton around 410 PM EDT.
South Lyon and Whitmore Lake around 430 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include
Lakeland, Island Lake State Recreation Area, and Chilson.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
